The VE did not vary significantly in response to spaceflight (or for ground controls) but the null result on going into space was actually surprising. We can model both the PU and SVV as being determined by a combination of gravity, body, and visual cues as a linear weighted sum of three vectors pointing in the directions signaled by each cue3 as:1\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
